#: {{ja-uxi|[[魚]][[や]][[肉]]'''等'''|さかな や にく '''など'''|fish and meat '''and things like that'''}}

=====Usage notes=====
* {{ja-uk|kana=hira|など}}
* For the ''et cetera'' sense, the reading ''tō'' is somewhat more formal than ''nado''. Spelling this term in hiragana is advantageous as it clearly distinguishes it from the formal Sino‐Japanese reading, preventing unintended shifts in tone and providing a visual cue for parsing lists.

